<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 6:51AM CDT  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...HEAT INDEX VALUES UP TO 108 DEGREES ON GALVESTON ISLAND THIS
AFTERNOON...
The combination of hot temperatures and humidity will result in
yet another day of near Heat Advisory conditions on Galveston
Island. Air temperatures will reach 94°F-95°F, but heat index
values will top out around 108°F in the afternoon. Practicing
heat safety is encouraged. Drink plenty of water, take frequent breaks
in the shade or indoors if working outside, avoid strenuous
outdoor activities during the hottest part of the day, and ALWAYS
look before you lock your vehicle.</description>
